This is another great adventure game in the same spirit as Myst. The puzzles have just the right balance of puzzle challenge and story that will meet most people's needs. Although I didn't make a lot of use of it, the in-game hints with optional solutions can keep you going if you really got stuck without disrupting the flow of the game. Need more games in this genre, a great follow up from "The Lost City". Fire Maple games going from strength to strength in this genre.

Unlike the other two this game's challenges were lacking. I found it to be extremely linear and too easily were all of the puzzles solved quickly. Perhaps this game was designed for a younger audience other than the grizzled veterans of the genre. Keeping that in mind I easily give this game a 4 star because it is still quality.

I played Lost City and was delighted to see another title from Fire Maple. This release is a bit shorter but I enjoyed the exploration and getting to open up new game areas as solutions were discovered.  A hint system is provided but it should be used with care, as spoilers may be revealed when you are just looking for a gentle nudge.  Mosaika is a return to a classic gaming style that brings back alot of great gaming memories for this adventurer!

Fire Maple Games has always put out amazing games and products - this one is bar none, the best of their entire series - the graphics, and scenery are warm and inviting - you feel as though you are embarking on a mystical adventure filled with fantasy, puzzles, and more - the environments are nothing short of breathtaking, and really immerse you into the world of Mosaika. The puzzles are much more challenging this time around, and really make you think of your next step - the nice thing about this game is that you have a magnifying glass hint button, so anytime you are stuck, just tap the magnifier, and it tells you the next step - if there is a puzzle involved, you even have the choice of revealing the solution, or waiting to see if you can solve it yourself. That's a really nice touch to this game so that both rookies and hardcores to the series can enjoy this game. I have yet to finish it, but Fire Maple delivers with this stunning 2D adventure game, well worth the price of entry and then some. Play this now, and it won't disappoint!!
